Parliament, Thursday, 17 December 2020 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) has noted the public concern over a structure that connects Nzondwane and Ndongane villages and the matter receives the attention of the committee. The committee has requested Nongoma Local Municipality where the structure is based to prepare a comprehensive report on the structure, a technical report, financial report as well as the terms of reference regarding the circumstances that led to the building of the structure. The committee will meet in January next year where it will determine a way forward on the structure. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR MKHULEKO HLENGWA. Unfortunately, the Chairperson is indisposed and will not be fielding any interviews. For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
